author: @geekdiggy
text:
since this was probably filmed weeks/months ago, and she's safely back in korea right now, i will do a friendly hawaiian tour guide preview!
0:05, 1:04 - magic island, part of ala moana beach park (just outside of waikiki). instagrammable picnic spot with jogging paths, snorkeling, a lagoon enclosed by a man-made rock wall (which she's standing on at 1:04) and lots of parking! aside from being a great place to watch the sunset, you can also watch the canoe races from here on sundays (or is it saturdays? i forget). but during the afternoons (1:15 up to around sunset ish) you can watch the canoe clubs practice out here sometimes.
0:07 - sitting outside cheesecake factory in waikiki (on kalakaua ave, near the royal hawaiian hotel where twice stayed on a visit last year, which is why i assume this was filmed on that visit)
0:09, 1:01 - about 25 minutes southeast of waikiki, this spot is called halona, but most people refer to it as Blowhole, named for a very dangerous lava tube nearby that shoots up huge geysers of water when the waves come in. some call it secret beach because it's located far below the nearby roadway, so if you're not paying attention you might drive right past it. this cove is where Twice shot their "Dance the Night Away" MV*
0:13 - halona lookout, above the cove. the narrow roadway has very few places to pull over and sight-see, so this parking lot is impossibly crowded at all hours of daylight. at night, it's the best makeout point on the island because it's dark, hardly anyone would think to go there (even the cops don't usually bother), and the stargazing is fantastic ;)
0:15, 0:43 - scenic point off the roadway outside of hanuama bay (more on that later). that imposing feature in the background is kokohead crater. i can't describe what a killer of a hike it is, so you're gonna have to youtube it. it's a monster.
0:17, 0:24, 3:38 - hanauma bay. it's a large cove near the two places i just described (these are all on the southeastern part of the island). it's a touristy snorkeling spot and it's sometimes really crowded, but the view is nice (0:20 obviously) and the water is great. plus it's relatively shallow so you don't have to worry too much about the sharks that may or may not be commuting in the deeper, darker waters a mile out at sea. yes, sharks exist, but they're almost almost almost never a problem, seriously.
0:21, 0:49, 1:00 - bellows beach on the east side of the island, another 20 minutes east of the previous spots. some of the most beautiful shoreline on the island. it's flat, the sand is powdery, the water is shallow and baby blue, the waves are friendly, it's always sunny (even when it rains, go figure) and the tall trees offer the perfect shade for picnics. if you want to know what a postcard looks like, this is it.
0:26 - i'm not gonna lie, i don't know if the snorkel gear at hanauma bay is sold or rented. i'm pretty sure it's rented, and that thought always grossed me out. i haven't been there since i was a kid, but i do sometimes go hiking on that hill in the background. it's a wonderful place. side note: i can't figure out if nayeon went on two different days or if she just changed her clothes at some point. don't know why she would have. you know she didn't go swimming😅
0:45 - 0:48, 0:57 - more about halona lookout: if you can't tell from all these clips, the southern tip of the island is windy as hell. anyway, from this observation point, if you look directly south you can see the island of moloka'i. it'll be the long, flat, tabletop-looking one. beyond that, on a clear day, you can see another bump on the horizon. there's some debate as to whether that's the island of maui or the island of lana'i, or both. i kid you not, to this day people still debate which one it is. don't ask me because i can't decide either!
1:11 - the text says "⬆여기 무지개 [rainbow here] ➡여기 초사이언 [super sayan here]" because of her hair lol
so that's it for this preview. i intend to update/elaborate/repeat as needed once the full series is posted. stay tuned!


since i know what y'all are thinking, i'll reiterate: this commentary is meant as a tour guide for anyone planning to come to the island of oahu (where all the idols go, because apparently they don't know about the other islands), or as a reminder for anyone who has been to oahu in the past, or is just looking to know more about the places shown in this video. sensibly, this couldn't be considered a safety issue, for two reasons: 1) these are very well-known and highly trafficked tourist spots, 2) she isn't there right now, and this was most likely filmed quite some time ago (perhaps the same time as jayeon tv? can other once verify that please?). i type these commentaries on every idol video i find that takes place on this island because i'm proud of the place i'm from and love to share it (you can check out my tour guides on the jayeontv videos) and wouldn't be doing it were it a risk to our precious fake maknae :)
